        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/49961",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rchouinard",
                        "name": "rchouinard",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Chouinard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This issue also affects deployment via Apache alias directives. I have several ZF1 applications working just fine deployed under http:\/\/domain.com\/app-name\/. Attempting to do the same with ZF2 fails to properly detect the baseUrl.\r\n\r\nA deployment of the ZF2 Skeleton Application to http:\/\/localhost\/zf2-skeleton\/ fails with the following stack trace:\r\n\r\n{noformat:title=Stack Trace}\r\n#0 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/library\/Zend\/Di\/Di.php(130): Zend\\Di\\Di->newInstance('zf2-skeleton', Array)\r\n#1 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/library\/Zend\/Mvc\/Application.php(332): Zend\\Di\\Di->get('zf2-skeleton')\r\n#2 [internal function]: Zend\\Mvc\\Application->dispatch(Object(Zend\\Mvc\\MvcEvent))\r\n#3 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/library\/Zend\/EventManager\/EventManager.php(441): call_user_func(Array, Object(Zend\\Mvc\\MvcEvent))\r\n#4 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/library\/Zend\/EventManager\/EventManager.php(202): Zend\\EventManager\\EventManager->triggerListeners('dispatch', Object(Zend\\Mvc\\MvcEvent), Object(Closure))\r\n#5 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/library\/Zend\/Mvc\/Application.php(251): Zend\\EventManager\\EventManager->trigger('dispatch', Object(Zend\\Mvc\\MvcEvent), Object(Closure))\r\n#6 \/var\/www\/html\/zf2-skeleton\/public\/index.php(28): Zend\\Mvc\\Application->run()\r\n#7 {main}\r\n{noformat}\r\n\r\nConverting the alias to a vhost and using http:\/\/zf2-skeleton.local\/ works just fine.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rchouinard",
                        "name": "rchouinard",
                        "displayName": "Ryan Chouinard",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-09T03:29:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-09T03:29:37.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50057",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dlukas",
                        "name": "dlukas",
                        "displayName": "David Lukas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The classname mentioned in the description should read Zend\\Http\\PhpEnvironment\\Request. I experience the same problem, ie it is impossible to deploy the ZF2 application into any virtual server subdirectory (alias). It works only when deployed into a vhost root.\r\n\r\nMy environment:\r\n - Windows 7\r\n - ZendServer CE 5.6.0\r\n - PHP 5.3.9\r\n - Apache\/2.2.21 (Win32) mod_ssl\/2.2.21 OpenSSL\/0.9.8o\r\n - ZF2 v2.0.0beta3\r\n\r\nhttpd.conf:\r\nAlias \/zf2tut \"c:\/WebDev\/PhpStorm\/ZF2Tutorial\/public\"\r\n<Directory \"c:\/WebDev\/PhpStorm\/ZF2Tutorial\/public\">\r\n  Options FollowSymLinks\r\n  Order Allow,Deny\r\n  Allow from All\r\n  AllowOverride All\r\n<\/Directory>\r\n\r\n.htaccess\r\nRewriteEngine On\r\nRewriteBase \/zf2tut\/\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -s [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -l [OR]\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} -d\r\nRewriteRule ^.*$ - [NC,L]\r\nRewriteRule ^.*$ index.php [NC,L]\r\n\r\nZend\\Http\\PhpEnvironment\\Request::detectBaseUrl() debug:\r\nSCRIPT_FILENAME = 'C:\/WebDev\/PhpStorm\/ZF2Tutorial\/public\/index.php'\r\nSCRIPT_NAME = '\/zf2tut\/index.php'\r\nPHP_SELF = '\/zf2tut\/index.php'\r\nORIG_SCRIPT_NAME = null\r\nreturn value = '' (on line 329), should be '\/zf2tut\/'",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dlukas",
                        "name": "dlukas",
                        "displayName": "David Lukas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-16T15:42:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-16T15:42:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50058",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bas",
                        "name": "bas",
                        "displayName": "Bas K",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A workaround is to set the base url in the index.php\r\n\r\n$application->getRequest()->setBaseUrl($appConfig['baseUrl']);\r\n\r\nor when using the ZendFrameworkSkeleton Application you can set base url when instantiating the view in the module...\r\n\r\npublic function initializeView($e) {\r\n        $app          = $e->getParam('application');\r\n\r\n        $app->getRequest()->setBaseUrl($e->getParam('config')->baseUrl);\r\n        $basePath     = $app->getRequest()->getBasePath();\r\n        $locator      = $app->getLocator();\r\n        $renderer     = $locator->get('Zend\\View\\Renderer\\PhpRenderer');\r\n        $renderer->plugin('basePath')->setBasePath($basePath);\r\n    }        \r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bas",
                        "name": "bas",
                        "displayName": "Bas K",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-03-16T16:01:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-03-16T16:01:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50336",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dlukas",
                        "name": "dlukas",
                        "displayName": "David Lukas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To circumvent this problem you can also use the DluBaseUrl: https:\/\/bitbucket.org\/dlu\/dlubaseurl (more info on it here: http:\/\/www.zfdaily.com\/2012\/04\/zf2-gets-the-baseurl-wrong\/). It encapsulates the Bas K's workaround in a simple ZF2 module.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=dlukas",
                        "name": "dlukas",
                        "displayName": "David Lukas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-04-19T14:00:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-04-19T14:00:18.000+0000"
                },
